<p><a name="Works_about_Ronald_Dworkin" id="Works_about_Ronald_Dworkin"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Ronald_Dworkin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Works about Ronald Dworkin">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Works about Ronald Dworkin</span></h3>
<p>Most contemporary books on jurisprudence give attention to some or all of Dworkin's views and arguments. The following books are devoted to assessing Dworkin's views and arguments.</p>
<ul>
<li>Marshall Cohen (ed.), <i>Ronald Dworkin and Contemporary Jurisprudence</i>. London: Duckworth, 1984.</li>
<li>Stephen Guest, <i>Ronald Dworkin</i>. Stanford: Stanford University Press, 1991.</li>
<li>Alan Hunt (ed.), <i>Reading Dworkin Critically</i>. New York and Oxford: Berg, 1992.</li>
<li>John J.A. Burke, <i>The Political Foundation of Law: The Need for Theory with Practical Value</i> (Austin &amp; Winfield 1992) (a comparative analysis between the political, legal and economic theories of Dworkin and Unger).</li>
<li>Justine Burley (ed.), <i>Dworkin and His Critics</i>. Oxford: Blackwell Publishing, 2004.</li>
<li>Scott Hershovitz (ed.), <i>Exploring Law's Empire: The Jurisprudence of Ronald Dworkin</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press, 2006.</li>
<li>Arthur Ripstein (ed.), <i>Ronald Dworkin</i>. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 2007.</li>
</ul>
<p>In French:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.philodroit.be/spip.php?page=auteur&amp;id_auteur=2&amp;lang=fr" class="external text" title="http://www.philodroit.be/spip.php?page=auteur&amp;id_auteur=2&amp;lang=fr" rel="nofollow">Julie Allard</a>, <i>Dworkin et Kant. Réflexions sur le jugement</i>, Bruxelles: Editions de l'ULB, 2001 <a href="http://www.editions-universite-bruxelles.be/ABWebBuilder.php?page=/catalogue/detail/,action=abcataloguedetail;displayouvrage;797" class="external text" title="http://www.editions-universite-bruxelles.be/ABWebBuilder.php?page=/catalogue/detail/,action=abcataloguedetail;displayouvrage;797" rel="nofollow">See the book</a></li>
